---
description: Enforce English language for PRs, reviews, and repository communication.
globs:
  - "**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

- All pull requests (titles, descriptions), commit messages, code comments, and review discussions must be written in English (prefer US English).
- Before creating or editing a PR, ensure any auto-generated content is translated/edited to English.
- Use clear, concise language; avoid regionalisms and non-English phrases.
- PR titles should use imperative mood and follow Conventional Commits when applicable.
- Summaries should be bullet-pointed, focusing on impact and testing instructions.

